Description: Federal contractor Green Bay Dressed Beef LLC agreed to pay $1.65 million in back wages, interest and benefits to 970 women who were allegedly subjected to systemic discrimination by the company. The settlement followed an investigation by the Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs, which found that the women were rejected for general laborer positions at the company's Green Bay plant in 2006 and 2007.
Agency: Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs
